# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# Tutorial 1 -- units/potential demonstration (solution only)
# Identical single-point energy to initial.lmp, but run in "real" units.
# Al_zhou.eam.alloy is written in "metal" units and carries a UNITS: tag,
# so LAMMPS automatically converts it to real units (energies x 23.060549).
# The single-point energy is therefore physically identical to the metal-unit
# result (-915.75277 eV = -21117.76 kcal/mol). Without the UNITS: tag, LAMMPS
# could not convert and would silently use the eV numbers as kcal/mol.

units real
dimension 3
boundary p p p
atom_style atomic

lattice fcc 4.05
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.05 4.05 4.05
region box block 0 4 0 4 0 4
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.2 16.2 16.2)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 256 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.2 16.2 16.2)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds

pair_style eam/alloy
pair_coeff * * Al_zhou.eam.alloy Al
Reading eam/alloy potential file Al_zhou.eam.alloy with DATE: 2007-10-12
WARNING: Converting eam/alloy potential in metal units to real units (src/potential_file_reader.cpp:300)

thermo_style custom step pe press lx
run 0
